Walton


James Carr Walton[1] (born June 7, 1948)[5] is the youngest son of Sam Walton, the founder of the world's largest retailer, Walmart. On the 2016 Forbes list of world billionaires, Jim Walton was ranked as #15 with a net worth of $33.6 billion.



